## 3. Implementation Task Breakdown

> [!NOTE]
> We will execute these tasks sequentially. Each phase must be tested before moving to the next.

*   **Phase 1: Database Schema & Core Entities**
    *   Update Prisma schema to include the new Application fields (e.g., `companyGtmChallenge`, `clientComments`, `aiPreScreenFlags`).
    *   Add Enums for `DiagnosisStatus` and `PaymentGateway`.
    *   Run Prisma migrations.
*   **Phase 2: Mock AI & Vetting Services (Backend)**
    *   Create `vetting.service.ts` to house the Mock LLM logic for Need Diagnosis and Opportunity Briefs.
    *   Create logic to parse domains from references and mock the LinkedIn API validations.
*   **Phase 3: Company Intake & Dashboard Updates (Frontend)**
    *   Update `app/(public)/apply/company/page.tsx` with the new optional template queries.
    *   Build the Admin view to review the AI Need Diagnosis.
    *   Build the Client Dashboard view to allow the client to read the diagnosis and add comments.
*   **Phase 4: Talent Vetting & Dashboard Updates (Frontend)**
    *   Update `app/(public)/apply/operator/page.tsx` with the new talent queries.
    *   Build the Admin view to read the AI Pre-Screen flags (e.g., Domain warnings, LinkedIn mock success).
*   **Phase 5: Payments & SoW Templates**
    *   Build out `STRIPE` and `RAZORPAY` mock checkout flow redirects based on the $50 / ₹15,000 rules.
    *   Populate the SoW endpoints with standard boilerplate text.
